snippet.title: Amber Heard Claims She Feared For Her Life After Johnny Depp 'Tried To Smother Her With Pillow
snippet.description:
Amber Heard claims she feared for her life after Johnny Depp 'tried to smother her with pillow

Heard said: “There was one severe ­incident in December 2015 when I truly feared for my life” 
 Amber Heard has claimed husband Johnny Depp tried to smother her with a pillow while drunk.

The actress said in legal papers: “I feared for my life.”

A pal of Amber has claimed Depp left his wife with facial injuries and a chunk of hair missing during a terrifying drunken attack.

Heard is said to have texted the pal for help after the film star allegedly tried to smother her with a pillow in a violent incident that left her “battered and bruised”.

The model and actress, 30, has released new photos showing injuries she claimed Depp inflicted on her during the alleged assault at their Los Angeles apartment in December last year.
As part of her legal action, in which she successfully applied for a restraining order, Heard said: “There was one severe ­incident in December 2015 when I truly feared for my life.”
Her friend backed her claim yesterday by saying: “I got to her apartment to find her with a cut and bruised lip, a swollen eye and a chunk of hair missing from the top of her head.

“This incident really stuck with me because she confided in me that day that she feared for her life after an intoxicated Johnny tried to suffocate her with a pillow.

“I have personally witnessed the aftermath of Johnny Depp’s violent and abusive behaviour towards her on many occasions.”

The friend’s comments in a US newspaper yesterday and the new photos in People magazine emerged just days after Heard claimed she was hit by iPhone thrown by Depp.
Last week she told a court she had not seen her husband of 15 months for about four weeks before he arrived at their home on May 21 “inebriated and high” – the day after the death of his mother, Betty Sue Palmer, 81.

After initially having a “peaceful conversation” about his mother’s death, she claimed Depp’s “demeanour changed dramatically” and he became “extremely angry”.

She said: “Johnny then grabbed the cell phone, wound up his arm like a baseball pitcher and threw the cell phone at me, striking my cheek and eye with great force.”
But despite providing pictures of her injuries, police are “adamant” they saw no marks on her when they attended the couple’s flat two weeks ago.

The officers spoke with their superiors on Tuesday afternoon and said they had no idea Depp was involved at all after the 911 call came in under the name Heard.

They said when they knocked at her door there had been a report of domestic dispute.

Heard greeted them through a crack but would not let them in.

They questioned her through the door and she said it was a simple verbal argument with her husband.

She never mentioned Hollywood star Depp, 52, by name. The officers told her they needed to make sure she was not declining help under duress, so they insisted on coming in and speaking with her.

Heard obliged, and the officers said they looked at her closely enough to determine there were no marks, swelling or bruising on her face or other exposed parts of her body.

She did not file a formal complaint at the time but her lawyers revealed this week that she had given a statement to detectives.

snippet.title: Amber Heard accepts the award for 'Woman of the Year' during the GQ ceremony (November 15, 2017)
snippet.description:
Accepting her award in Sydney - which Heard joked was “on behalf of my dogs?” - the actress spoke out about her sexuality, and how the marriage equality vote has impacted her personally.
“I feel really honoured to be in this room tonight with examples of real gentlemen, it's a rare thig these days, and I feel honoured. “I also think the timing is amazing today: I flew in from Los Angeles after being here for eight months shooting, I thought I had finally escaped...but no. Two days later I flew back to accept this award...I'm assuming on behalf of my dogs Pistal and Boo. Well ufortunately they could not make it tonight.

“I was on the plane [to Sydney on Wednesday morning] and we were landing and the pilot came on the speaker and said, "Welcome to Sydney... and by the way, we just got news that the vote came in… and the majority of Australians support the right for all Australians to marry the person they love." And I thought this is a commercial airline, and the pilot is announcing this news, and wow that's brave. And then something unbelievable happened: the whole plane erupted in this chorus of applause [...] Every single person on the plane clapped,” she added. 
Remembering a time when being opening gay or lesbian wasn’t ok, Heard recalls a time she was warned about being involved with another woman - and how it still impacts her to this day. 
“I remember ten years ago when I refused to drop my girlfriend’s hand at the time, everyone told me that was a death sentence in Hollywood. Ten years late the whole plane is clapping at this offhanded news announcement that the pilot decided to make, and it brought chills to my body and a tear to my eye - and here I am.”

“So I feel really lucky to be here today, and I feel really honoured and humbled. And I appreciate it very much.”
@GQ Australia

-------------

snippet.title: Heartland To Go Off-Air? |Heartland Series
snippet.description:
#HeartlandSeries #AmberMarshall #AmyFleming
Hello heartland fans, how is everything going on? Welcome back to our channel UPCOMING SHOW. 
Heartland, one of the longest running Canadian series, has recently completed its 15th season and what we have felt is it is missing its originality. For all these seasons, though only few actors and characters have changed but absence of one character, exit of one actor from the show has completely changed the landscapes of heartland. yes we are talking about graham wardle aka ty borden of heartland. after graham’s exit from the show, the show has completely changed from overwhelming romantic family drama to depressive boring normal series. heartland was fan favourite all because of amy and ty and the base of its legacy was the story of amy and ty. Now since ty is absent its legacy is also almost gone.  So there are rumors that heartland 16 will be its last installment. It has been rumored that due to decresing trp and audiences loosing interest in the show, the makers and the channel cbc network has decided the show to go off air after heartland 16. So considering this we might not see heartland after upcoming season but, on a positive aspect, we might see return of ty borden in the show. Yes, you heard it right, if season 16 will be the last one, then it is possible that the makers would hear fans demand, and bring ty back. They could use the storyline of ty’s ghost coming to heartland, or ty coming in amy’s dream or better than that everything that had happened in season 13 was amy’s dream. Amy dreamt all those things but in reaity it never happened, ty was never shot and everything was back to normal. Or they can make a story that  amy had gone to coma after bullet hit her and everything she saw was just her nightmare and whe she wakes up from the coma she sees ty sitting next to her taking lindy in his lap along with the entire family.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp And Amber Heard in Marriage Split | Latest News World 2
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp And Amber Heard in Marriage Split | Latest News World 2
====================================================
Follow On Twitter:https://twitter.com/Latestnew2
====================================================
Follow On Pinterest:https://in.pinterest.com/LatestNewsWorld/
====================================================
Film star Johnny Depp and his actress wife Amber Heard are to divorce, US court documents have revealed.
Heard, 30, filed for divorce in Los Angeles Superior Court citing irreconcilable differences.
They married 15 months ago and have no children.
They have recently been embroiled in a legal case in Australia after Heard took two dogs into the country illegally. She pleaded guilty in April to a charge of falsifying documents.
Depp, 52, and Heard met while co-starring in the 2011 film The Rum Diary.
In the court papers, Texan-born Heard listed the separation date as Sunday.
Celebrity news website TMZ reported that Depp had asked a judge to reject Heard's claim for spousal support.
The split comes days after the death of Depp's mother. His latest film, Alice Through the Looking Glass, is due to be released on Friday.
Johnny Depp And Amber Heard in Marriage Split | Latest News World 2
The Australian court case started last year when Heard brought two dogs into the country where her husband was filming the latest movie in the Pirates of the Caribbean series.
When the case was settled, the couple released a video apology expressing remorse and advising travellers to respect Australian quarantine laws.
However, Australia's Deputy PM Barnaby Joyce had threatened to have the dogs put down, triggering a war of words with Depp that lasted for months.
The actor recently said on a US TV show that Mr Joyce looks "somehow inbred with a tomato".
Mr Joyce responded by saying he was "pulling strings" in Johnny Depp's head, like film villain Hannibal Lecter.

snippet.localized.description:
Johnny Depp And Amber Heard in Marriage Split | Latest News World 2
====================================================
Follow On Twitter:https://twitter.com/Latestnew2
====================================================
Follow On Pinterest:https://in.pinterest.com/LatestNewsWorld/
====================================================
Film star Johnny Depp and his actress wife Amber Heard are to divorce, US court documents have revealed.
Heard, 30, filed for divorce in Los Angeles Superior Court citing irreconcilable differences.
They married 15 months ago and have no children.
They have recently been embroiled in a legal case in Australia after Heard took two dogs into the country illegally. She pleaded guilty in April to a charge of falsifying documents.
Depp, 52, and Heard met while co-starring in the 2011 film The Rum Diary.
In the court papers, Texan-born Heard listed the separation date as Sunday.
Celebrity news website TMZ reported that Depp had asked a judge to reject Heard's claim for spousal support.
The split comes days after the death of Depp's mother. His latest film, Alice Through the Looking Glass, is due to be released on Friday.
Johnny Depp And Amber Heard in Marriage Split | Latest News World 2
The Australian court case started last year when Heard brought two dogs into the country where her husband was filming the latest movie in the Pirates of the Caribbean series.
When the case was settled, the couple released a video apology expressing remorse and advising travellers to respect Australian quarantine laws.
However, Australia's Deputy PM Barnaby Joyce had threatened to have the dogs put down, triggering a war of words with Depp that lasted for months.
The actor recently said on a US TV show that Mr Joyce looks "somehow inbred with a tomato".
Mr Joyce responded by saying he was "pulling strings" in Johnny Depp's head, like film villain Hannibal Lecter.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Faces Backlash for Tweet About ICE Checkpoints
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Faces Backlash for Tweet About ICE Checkpoints:
http://www.instyle.com/news/amber-heard-backlash-ice-tweet.

Thanks for watching, subscribe for more videos:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCStnChYQHsa2Uhl-y121BdQ?sub_confirmation=1
 In an effort to take a stand against Donald Trump's "zero tolerance" immigration policy, tweeted a message that many followers have called out as racist.    Early Tuesday morning, Heard posted about an ICE checkpoint near her L.A. home, writing, “Just heard there’s an ICE checkpoint in Hollywood, a few blocks from where I live. Everyone better give their housekeepers, nannies and landscapers a ride home tonight…” The tweet has since been deleted.    The issue? The message played into the stereotype that service-workers, such as housekeepers, nannies, and landscapers, would need to worry about an ICE checkpoint because of their legal status, reinforcing the idea that all or most people who hold such jobs arrived in the country illegally. Some followers also accused the actress of relegating all immigrants to the roles of "the help."    She continued, “Checkpoints on your home streets…. Is this the ‘great’ America we’re aiming for? Raids, fences and police-state like checkpoints don’t feel like the ‘land of the free’ our immigrant ancestors built.”   Heard's message may have been sent with the best intentions—to warn people near and dear to her friends and neighbors that they may be in danger—but her delivery got in the way. Followers swiftly called on her to reconsider her comments. They explained that even if she meant the message to come across as a tad satirical—meaning to drag her neighbors for living lives of excess with hired help—the post ultimately comes across as racist and aloof.    Following the backlash, Heard took down the original tweet and posted a new message lamenting that "it is hard to make a simple statement w/out it being used to distract from the real issues."    Though her original message was muddled on Twitter, Heard's recent political activism points to just a poor choice of words this time. On Instagram, the 32-year-old has highlighted a variety of organization working to further women’s reproductive rights, plus the work of the United Nations Human Rights Council. She also recently headed to Texas to protest President Trump’s immigration policy, and promoted the Families Belong Together rallies against it.    Judging by Heard's recent posts, it's easier to give her the benefit of the doubt. But still, it served as another reminder to think before you tweet.   Show Transcript  [MUSIC] [BLANK_AUDIO]   [MUSIC] [BLANK_AUDIO]
